# Garage door server

Django implementation of a garage door opener system.

Security works through a challenge response system.  

## Prepare the Pi

```
sudo apt update
sudo apt install git memcached python3-pip
sudo systemctl start memcached
sudo systemctl enable memcached
```

## Install the Required Modules

```
sudo pip3 install rpi-gpio Django==2.2.5 python-memcached
```

## If using Twilio

```
sudo pip3 install twilio
```

## Clone and configure the server

```
cd /opt
sudo mkdir garage_door_server
sudo chown pi garage_door_server/

git clone https://github.com/jeidon/garage_door_server.git

cd garage_door_server
```

### Setup settings

```
cd pysite
cp example.settings.py settings.py
```

### Edit the settings as needed 

Change SECRET_KEY and the OPEN_PIN, CLOSE_PIN, and OUTPUT_PIN values to match your own

```
cd ..

./manage.py migrate

./manage.py enable_download_magic_key SHORT_CHALLENGE
./manage.py runserver YOUR_IP:8000
```

## Setup for the phone

Enter SHORT_CHALLENGE
You're now setup

